      "updated_at": "1970-01-01T00:00:00Z",
      "valid_scope": "section_pair",
      "why_conflicting": "Authentication mandates session expiry after 24 hours of inactivity, while Session Retention Policy mandates sessions must not be terminated before a 30-day window. These rules directly contradict each other: a session idle for more than 24 hours would be expired by the authentication rule but must remain active per the retention policy.",
      "why_llm_cannot_decide": "Whether the 30-day retention applies to the session object in storage (audit record) or to the live authenticated session is a business/compliance design decision. The Purpose and Core Concept do not specify the scope of 'session' across these two sections. Only the project owner can determine whether 'retained and kept active' means a live login session or an audit log record."
    },
    {
      "base_source_hashes": [
        {
          "hash": "d4eb3e64eb3f7967f68aa03b573494928d5b35d426155a3141a8f735770e5932",
          "source_ref": "docs/spec/sample.md#0005-session-retention-policy"
        },
        {
          "hash": "1a3addf414634968c32e361e576a8ad06a84c0ef1a7a1170d35e9b22f8bf4756",
          "source_ref": "docs/spec/sample.md#0006-account-lockout"
        },
        {
          "hash": "990acca6acc83466e32ea730efba95ff4f5cadddb716751355ba26615a18f48b",
          "source_ref": "docs/core/purpose.md"
        },
        {
          "hash": "b5c8c7e3e58676afe4837cb64a7715467f7f3d4cbd098a5c0f4cb7f8b499d3e5",
          "source_ref": "docs/core/concept.md"
        }
      ],
      "conflict_id": "section_pair:sha256:v1:82384a4015ee312181087d08fa6c7058cfe86243db5e36c700ddb78ca69d6d75",
      "conflict_points": [
        {
          "left_excerpt": "Sessions must not be terminated before the 30-day retention window has elapsed.",
          "right_excerpt": "After 3 consecutive failed login attempts, the account is locked for 30 minutes. During a lockout period, all further login attempts are rejected immediately without incrementing the rate-limit counter.",
          "severity": "medium",
          "why_conflicting": "The retention policy prohibits session termination within 30 days, while the lockout policy rejects all login attempts for 30 minutes. If a lockout causes or is interpreted to cause active session invalidation, it would violate the retention constraint. The sections do not define their interaction."
        }
      ],
      "created_at": "1970-01-01T00:00:00Z",
      "recommended_next_action": "Add a clarifying sentence to either the Session Retention Policy or Account Lockout section specifying whether an account lockout terminates, suspends, or leaves unaffected any currently active sessions.",
      "related_sections": [],
      "section_pair": {
        "candidate_origin": "all_pairs",
        "left_section_id": "docs/spec/sample.md#0005-session-retention-policy",
        "right_section_id": "docs/spec/sample.md#0006-account-lockout",
        "section_pair_id": "section_pair:sha256:v1:82384a4015ee312181087d08fa6c7058cfe86243db5e36c700ddb78ca69d6d75"
      },
      "severity": "medium",
      "source_refs": [
