      ],
      "stale_dismissal": false,
      "status": "pending",
      "updated_at": "1970-01-01T00:00:00Z",
      "valid_scope": "section_pair",
      "why_conflicting": "Session Retention Policy mandates that sessions must be kept active and must not be terminated for a minimum of 30 days regardless of inactivity. Account Lockout states that after 3 failed login attempts the account is locked for 30 minutes and all further login attempts are rejected. The conflict is whether a lockout event constitutes or triggers session termination: the retention policy prohibits any session termination within 30 days, but a lockout may implicitly invalidate or suppress active sessions. The two sections do not define how they interact.",
      "why_llm_cannot_decide": "The Core Concept and Purpose describe this fixture as a minimal smoke-check sample intended to avoid triggering LLM conflict detection. However, the semantic overlap between 'sessions must not be terminated' (retention) and 'all further login attempts are rejected immediately' (lockout) leaves ambiguous whether lockout affects in-flight sessions or only blocks new authentication. Neither Purpose nor Core Concept defines the relationship between session lifecycle and account lockout state. A human author must clarify whether lockout suppresses, suspends, or is orthogonal to active sessions."
    },
    {
      "base_source_hashes": [
        {
          "hash": "3f4a7e5094a0ca51eeaf30da2a50d05fb2cd177a9ee6d303552882ecd37f49de",
