      "stale_dismissal": false,
      "status": "pending",
      "updated_at": "1970-01-01T00:00:00Z",
      "valid_scope": "section_pair",
      "why_conflicting": "Session Termination mandates automatic purge after 24 hours of inactivity, while Session Retention Policy mandates that all session records must be kept active for a minimum of 30 days regardless of inactivity. These two requirements directly contradict each other: a session inactive for 25 hours would be purged under Section A but must still be retained under Section B.",
      "why_llm_cannot_decide": "Both sections express mandatory constraints ('automatically purged' vs 'must be retained … minimum of 30 days … must not be terminated'). Neither Purpose nor Core Concept provides a priority rule between operational session lifecycle and compliance-driven retention. Resolving this requires a human decision on whether the 30-day retention applies to the live session object, an archived record, or a separate audit log, and which policy takes precedence when they conflict."
    }
  ],
